00:53:16,060 --> 00:53:20,940
<i>I try my best to hide my tears, but</i>

744
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:28,669
<i>They're exposed when I stand before you</i>

745
00:53:28,670 --> 00:53:33,500
<i>Even though I painfully push you away</i>

746
00:53:34,360 --> 00:53:39,220
<i>You're always at the same
place in my heart</i>

747
00:53:39,928 --> 00:53:42,843
<i>I'm in front of your apartment.
Come out for a minute.</i>

748
00:53:43,242 --> 00:53:44,117
Who...

749
00:53:44,237 --> 00:53:45,237
My little sister.

750
00:53:47,508 --> 00:53:48,659
Jae In.

751
00:53:53,070 --> 00:53:55,065
Thanks. I'll enjoy eating it.

752
00:54:00,410 --> 00:54:04,760
<i>Because your scent still lingers in me</i>

753
00:54:05,080 --> 00:54:10,270
<i>I cannot forget you yet</i>

754
00:54:11,780 --> 00:54:16,000
<i>I can still feel your tears</i>

755
00:54:16,290 --> 00:54:21,010
<i>I guess I'm still hurt that much</i>

756
00:54:21,865 --> 00:54:26,039
I'll make you lots of
tasty things when you're back.

757
00:54:27,409 --> 00:54:30,693
I'll bring lots of tasty things, so...

758
00:54:35,511 --> 00:54:37,352
<i>make sure you come back.</i>

759
00:54:38,591 --> 00:54:41,276
I don't care about the condition
that you're in.

760
00:54:41,396 --> 00:54:44,452
I don't care even if you laugh
like an idiot,

761
00:54:44,572 --> 00:54:46,923
and I don't care even if you can't
recognize me, so...

762
00:54:47,043 --> 00:54:48,657
come back quickly.

763
00:54:51,685 --> 00:54:54,569
Let's eat together for sure this time.

764
00:54:57,190 --> 00:55:01,899
<i>I guess my never-ending love for you</i>

765
00:55:01,900 --> 00:55:09,030
<i>would not let me send you away yet</i>

766
00:55:15,561 --> 00:55:16,926
What?

767
00:55:17,448 --> 00:55:19,121
Shim Gun Wook is alive?

768
00:55:19,241 --> 00:55:20,241
Where is he?

769
00:55:20,361 --> 00:55:21,922
<i>He was in a nursing home in Kangwon County.</i>

770
00:55:22,042 --> 00:55:24,485
<i>He's been admitted under
the name Hong Tae Seong, too.</i>

771
00:55:24,822 --> 00:55:28,582
But Madam, I think he's mentally ill.

772
00:55:28,702 --> 00:55:30,393
<i>I don't think he's normal right now.</i>

773
00:55:30,921 --> 00:55:32,241
Should I just let him be?

774
00:55:32,361 --> 00:55:33,238
No.

775
00:55:34,128 --> 00:55:36,737
What happens if he regains his sanity?

776
00:55:37,305 --> 00:55:40,558
The source of trouble should
be sliced away with a clean cut.

777
00:55:50,878 --> 00:55:51,799
<i>Father.</i>

778
00:55:53,197 --> 00:55:56,066
I can call you Father, right? Even still...

779
00:55:57,355 --> 00:55:59,519
<i>Why didn't she tell me a little bit later?</i>

780
00:55:59,933 --> 00:56:04,786
Anyway, Madam Shin and I catch
each other at the worst moments.

781
00:56:06,382 --> 00:56:08,653
Can't I be with you a bit longer?

782
00:56:13,668 --> 00:56:14,624
Father...

783
00:56:17,192 --> 00:56:23,094
we grew close to each other
while you raised me?

784
00:56:24,155 --> 00:56:26,631
I haven't done anything for you yet.

785
00:56:27,997 --> 00:56:30,176
<i>Do you still have something you want?</i>

786
00:56:33,137 --> 00:56:34,503
<i>Uncle!</i>

787
00:56:41,933 --> 00:56:43,529
So Dam, where have you been?

788
00:56:44,377 --> 00:56:45,221
A kiss?

789
00:56:46,893 --> 00:56:48,627
<i>Have you been listening to your mom?</i>

790
00:56:50,150 --> 00:56:52,329
I finally understand...

791
00:56:52,805 --> 00:56:55,383
why you treated me so cruelly,

792
00:56:55,503 --> 00:56:58,487
why you gave me the cold shoulder.

793
00:57:00,712 --> 00:57:01,909
Mother, I...

794
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:04,180
Don't call me Mother.

795
00:57:05,269 --> 00:57:08,500
You and I are completely unrelated.

796
00:57:09,896 --> 00:57:10,710
Mother.

797
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:15,605
Do you know why I didn't
go to my biological mother?

798
00:57:16,878 --> 00:57:18,459
I bet it was the money.

799
00:57:21,979 --> 00:57:22,869
No.

800
00:57:25,109 --> 00:57:29,523
Because the two of you at least
didn't throw me away.

801
00:57:31,902 --> 00:57:37,050
So I thought there would
be a day I'd repay that favor.

802
00:57:37,170 --> 00:57:39,481
I told myself I would, even if I
were to leave.

803
00:57:39,601 --> 00:57:43,207
But...
it seems like I can't even do that now.

804
00:57:48,333 --> 00:57:50,742
I have no reason to feel sorry for you.

805
00:57:51,156 --> 00:57:54,233
We gave you the best lifestyle
you could have ever had.

806
00:57:58,979 --> 00:58:00,130
I'm sorry, Mother.

807
00:58:02,892 --> 00:58:07,481
I didn't even realize that you
raised me all this while, and...

808
00:58:10,663 --> 00:58:12,673
I only got angry all time.

809
00:58:14,269 --> 00:58:16,356
I should've been better to you much earlier.

810
00:58:19,921 --> 00:58:22,775
I knew from the moment
I first came into this house.

811
00:58:25,522 --> 00:58:28,238
That no one loved me.

812
00:58:28,509 --> 00:58:31,133
That no one accepted me as a part
of the family.

813
00:58:32,645 --> 00:58:36,301
I waited, thinking it was hard
for everyone...

814
00:58:36,421 --> 00:58:41,086
to open up their hearts again
after the boy before me left, but...

815
00:58:43,070 --> 00:58:48,521
if I'd known back then that everyone
couldn't love me...

816
00:58:51,114 --> 00:58:53,524
it actually would've been easier for me.

817
00:58:57,346 --> 00:58:59,478
Your father loved you.

818
00:59:06,108 --> 00:59:08,007
Those words are...

819
00:59:10,662 --> 00:59:13,669
the most kind, among all the things
you've ever said, Mother.

820
00:59:24,077 --> 00:59:25,289
I'll be off.

821
00:59:45,501 --> 00:59:48,171
<i>A tadpole by the creek</i>

822
00:59:48,447 --> 00:59:50,549
Squiggle, squiggle

823
00:59:50,669 --> 00:59:51,777
While he was swimming

824
00:59:51,897 --> 00:59:53,265
Pop! the hind legs come out

825
00:59:53,385 --> 00:59:54,647
<i>Pop! the front legs come out</i>

826
00:59:54,767 --> 00:59:57,933
Hop! Hop! It's become a frog!

827
00:59:58,053 --> 00:59:59,835
Squiggle, squiggle

828
00:59:59,955 --> 01:00:02,895
<i>Squiggle, squiggle
Squiggle, squiggle</i>

829
01:00:03,524 --> 01:00:05,836
<i>While it was swimming</i>

830
01:00:05,956 --> 01:00:07,521
<i>Pop! the hind legs come out</i>

831
01:00:07,766 --> 01:00:10,053
Pop! the front legs come out

832
01:00:10,173 --> 01:00:12,078
<i>Hop! Hop! It's become a frog!</i>

833
01:00:12,976 --> 01:00:14,065
Tae Seong.

834
01:00:15,078 --> 01:00:16,413
Don't sympathize with me.

835
01:00:17,257 --> 01:00:18,822
I really hate that.

836
01:00:18,942 --> 01:00:20,247
It's nothing like that.

837
01:00:20,723 --> 01:00:21,889
Eat before you go.

838
01:00:22,196 --> 01:00:23,255
See?

839
01:00:23,730 --> 01:00:25,449
You're sympathizing with me already.

840
01:00:31,894 --> 01:00:33,842
I should cut my ties...

841
01:00:35,423 --> 01:00:37,495
and go my own way now.

842
01:00:40,241 --> 01:00:41,070
I'm going.

843
01:00:43,606 --> 01:00:44,573
Tae Seong.

844
01:01:19,830 --> 01:01:20,674
Tae Seong.

845
01:01:27,376 --> 01:01:28,941
Where are you going?

846
01:01:30,890 --> 01:01:33,192
Can't I go with you?

847
01:01:33,680 --> 01:01:34,570
What?

848
01:01:34,690 --> 01:01:37,179
You're going to meet Shim Gun Wook,
aren't you?

849
01:01:38,898 --> 01:01:43,118
I also have a lot of things to
talk about with him.

850
01:02:30,012 --> 01:02:31,193
Father.

851
01:02:33,894 --> 01:02:36,718
I've left my seat empty for too long.

852
01:02:38,164 --> 01:02:42,461
I'll get it back soon and give it
to Tae Ra or Mo Ne.

853
01:02:48,708 --> 01:02:50,949
It would've been nice if Tae Gyun
were here too.

854
01:02:53,573 --> 01:02:55,967
As you always used to say,

855
01:02:56,087 --> 01:03:02,047
"If you can achieve something great, then
don't think about how the process may be. "

856
01:03:04,776 --> 01:03:09,994
Shin Myung Won will keep this seat safe,
so please don't worry.

857
01:03:17,536 --> 01:03:18,963
<i>I've arrived, ma'am.</i>

858
01:03:20,037 --> 01:03:21,618
<i>I'll take care of it without a trace.</i>

859
01:03:21,738 --> 01:03:24,334
Please make sure to take care
of it this time.

860
01:03:25,540 --> 01:03:27,304
Call me when you're finished.

861
01:04:42,981 --> 01:04:43,993
<i>You're here, ma'am?</i>

862
01:05:02,953 --> 01:05:04,165
Hello?

863
01:05:05,976 --> 01:05:06,851
What?

864
01:05:08,431 --> 01:05:10,472
Shim Gun Wook has disappeared?

871
01:05:37,364 --> 01:05:39,320
<i>The only grief you feel
is for being tricked, right?</i>

872
01:05:39,458 --> 01:05:42,971
Then what about Gun Wook's tragic life?

873
01:05:44,411 --> 01:05:45,435
I'm sorry, Tae Seong.

874
01:05:47,303 --> 01:05:50,986
<i>Why are you doing this to us?
Why are you doing this to me?</i>

875
01:05:51,370 --> 01:05:53,472
I won't come see you anymore.

876
01:05:53,613 --> 01:05:56,053
<i>I threw away the real one
and brought in a fake.</i>

877
01:05:56,298 --> 01:05:59,766
<i>In the end, you lost your parents,
your brothers and everything.</i>

878
01:05:59,886 --> 01:06:02,851
<i>Sometimes, even I don't know who I am.</i>

879
01:06:02,971 --> 01:06:05,168
<i>Who will call me?</i>

880
01:06:05,885 --> 01:06:08,724
<i>And which name will they call me with?</i>

881
01:06:10,460 --> 01:06:16,080
<i>would not let me send you away yet</i>

882
01:06:26,200 --> 01:06:30,350
<i>Because your scent still lingers in me</i>

883
01:06:30,760 --> 01:06:36,040
<i>I cannot forget you yet</i>

884
01:06:37,690 --> 01:06:41,700
<i>I can still feel your tears</i>

885
01:06:42,110 --> 01:06:47,520
<i>I guess I'm still hurt that much</i>

886
01:06:47,630 --> 01:06:51,090
<i>I always wander about your place</i>

887
01:06:52,153 --> 01:06:54,117
<i>The alien ET...</i>

888
01:06:54,237 --> 01:06:55,767
<i>he had supernatural powers,
but they were all friends.</i>

889
01:06:55,887 --> 01:06:56,776
Hoy hoy.

890
01:06:56,896 --> 01:06:57,792
Hoy hoy.

891
01:06:57,912 --> 01:06:59,632
<i>Why can't I have a Gumiho friend?</i>

892
01:06:59,752 --> 01:07:00,802
[My Girlfriend is a Gumiho]

893
01:07:00,922 --> 01:07:02,072
The fox has disappeared!

894
01:07:02,192 --> 01:07:03,269
<i>Why are you doing this to me?</i>

895
01:07:03,389 --> 01:07:04,474
<i>I liked you?</i>

896
01:07:04,594 --> 01:07:05,656
<i>How can I pull that off?</i>

897
01:07:05,776 --> 01:07:06,991
<i>You can't let me go.</i>

898
01:07:07,111 --> 01:07:08,326
You're mine.

899
01:07:08,894 --> 01:07:10,520
Why me, why?!

900
01:07:10,640 --> 01:07:11,671
You're looking for information, right?

901
01:07:11,791 --> 01:07:13,512
The person you are desperately seeking,

902
01:07:13,632 --> 01:07:15,748
is currently at Dongbo Charcoal Grill.

903
01:07:17,145 --> 01:07:18,526
<i>It's really not a big deal like I thought.</i>

904
01:07:18,646 --> 01:07:19,892
<i>Will we be able to catch her alive?</i>

905
01:07:20,012 --> 01:07:21,702
- Dae Yong!
- Don't come any closer!

906
01:07:21,822 --> 01:07:24,296
<i>You stayed alive because of me,
but now you'll die.</i>

907
01:07:25,353 --> 01:07:26,983
[My Girlfriend is a Gumiho]